<br>
In my experience, the NUMBER ONE limiting factor for me in these fights isn't mana pool or short run DPS (especially with the nuke focus ring and zero-casting time rightclicks to refresh spells): its aggro. I will end these fights well above 20%, sometimes above 40%  because if I tried to nuke any more I'd risk gaining aggro; thereby at best getting summoned and killed, worst force the mob out of position. This isn't just a theoretical claim: I've tried experiementing. I've fought zlandicar, rhag 1, Hoshkar, some other mobs &quot;properly&quot; using nukes judiciously to avoid gaining aggro, and ending the fight at 40-60 mana, and then I've tried to glide down to zero mana using any means necessary, and I get summoned and killed. <p>Master Cydmab Promethean, Triune <BR>
